Text.string: Believe it or not, this used to be a nice neighborhood.
Maliwan has taken so much from us. But that Katagawa bastard doesn't even care—he doesn't even see it! All he sees is a merger.
As if things weren't bad enough already, now on top of everything, we've got the COV to deal with? Slag me, I'm sick of this war.
Rhys may seem like he's in over his mustachioed head sometimes, but he's actually doing a pretty good job at this, all things considered.
At any rate, we're sure as hell lucky that you showed up when you did. Glad to have you onboard, Vault Hunter.
Looks like you picked up some new friends. That's good. We could use all the help we can get.
I hear Athenas has been its own kind of mess. If it's anything like what we're dealing with down here, I'm sure they're glad you showed up when you did.
Looks like this war is spilling out past Promethea, huh? Too bad for them. I wouldn't wish this crap on anyone.
Maliwan don't care who they step on, do they? Civilians on Promethea, civilians on Athenas... I guess dead civilians are just another speed bump to the Maliwan war machine.
These bloody mercenaries, waging war in MY city for a damn paycheck? Unbelievable.
YES! With Katagawa dead, maybe we can actually start getting things back to normal around here.
The fight's not over yet, but killing Katagawa sure puts us a big step ahead in this thing.
So, you're finally gonna go track down that Vault you've been after? Well done, well done.
I gotta say it again. You're my new absolute bloody hero for taking Katagawa off the board.
Tide's turned. Time to start rebuilding my city.
I am so, so sorry to hear about your friend. My condolences.
I'm sorry, I... I don't know what else to say.
I know you've got to head off to Eden-6 now, but we're never gonna forget what you did for us here.
Atlas is on the right track now. It'll be nice to get back to normal around here... y'know, eventually.
Rebuilding this city is gonna take a lot of time. But I know my people are up to it.
It's not easy, you know? Going from barista to guerrilla fighter overnight.
Hey, I'm as surprised as anyone that I'm any good at this.
Who knows, maybe someday you'll get to meet the real me... y'know, the me that's got nothing to do with the war.
I am so tired of fighting. All I want is a decent night's sleep.
Promethea was finally crawling out of the gutter, really becoming a decent planet again. Then Maliwan thought better of it.
Whatever you maniacs did on Pandora, we saw it from here. But you're alive, so I guess it worked?
Looks like we're off to a good start here, Hunter.
How was Athenas? Occupied and totally beautiful, I'm guessing.
You wrecked that bastard's pleasure yacht?! Hahaha!
Hell yeah! You took that Katagawa bastard DOWN! Love it!
So, if we take that intersection down the way, we could set up roadblocks and maintain control over this whole area.
Maliwan troops stomping all over my bloody neighborhood... Makes me sick.
We may not have the numbers, but this is our home. And we'll take it back no matter what.
Things were bad enough around here before we had to deal with bandits, too. Guh.
I could really go for a coffee right now.
Got a new job here.
Need for you for a quick gig.
New mission ready for ya.
Hello there, Hunter.
Oh, hey!
Hunter, good to see you.
Always nice to see a friendly face.
Hey-hey!
Please don't tell me you just walked in here holding a poxy Maliwan.
Are you REALLY using a Maliwan right now?
Got a job for you.
You got time for a job?
Got a mission here I could use you on.
Mission for ya, if you're up to it.
Could you do me a favor?
How's that job going?
Don't you have a job to do?
Job's going all right, then?
D'you think you'll have that job done soon?
I'll be right here when you're done with that job.
Right, later.
Sure sure, catch you later.
See ya soon.
Catch up with you later.
Bye then.
Yep.
Okay.
Jog on, then.
Stay safe.
See some Maliwan, you give 'em some bullets for me, will you?
